## Stable Facts

- 2026-07-18: Cloudflare temporary account provisioning can finish the PoW step and then return 504 from `/provisioning/previews`. The plugin pins its verified Wrangler version and retries only explicit temporary-account creation 429/502/503/504 failures with bounded 2s/5s backoff; unrelated upload/deploy errors remain single-attempt.

- 2026-07-18: `drop.szlk.ai` stores website share bytes and private metadata in the `solodrop-previews` R2 bucket. Guest shares support 1, 7, or 30 days; signed-in users can also keep a share until deletion. Expired URLs return 410 immediately and an hourly scheduled task removes expired R2 objects.
- 2026-07-18: Website share pages support PDF, DOCX and PPTX browser previews, optional repeated text watermarks, and an optional download action. Disabling download removes the UI action and makes the explicit download endpoint return 403, but is a presentation control rather than DRM because preview bytes still reach the browser.
- 2026-07-18: SZLKlaws recognizes `solodrop` and publishes English/Chinese product supplements describing the public-link, temporary-account, no-file-custody, activity-retention and claim-credential boundaries.
- 2026-07-18: The public site uses `/` for Chinese and `/en` for English. Both routes cover sharing, account and legal journeys; reciprocal hreflang/canonical metadata, sitemap entries and matching FAQ/application schema are live.

- 2026-07-16: Project repository is `/home/ubuntu/project/solodrop`, with remote `https://github.com/jobssteve164dev/solodrop` and primary branch `main`.
- 2026-07-16: SoloDrop is a VS Code extension that turns local agent artifacts into browser previews, verifies the deployed URL and copies the public link. Its primary sidebar entry supports drag-and-drop, active-editor selection, file picker and Explorer context sharing.
- 2026-07-16: The first release supports Markdown, text/code/JSON, images, PDF, CSV and HTML. It scans common credential patterns and keeps Cloudflare claim URLs separate from public preview URLs.
- 2026-07-16: Release `v0.0.4` is published to Visual Studio Marketplace and Open VSX as `SZLK.solodrop`; the GitHub release contains `solodrop-0.0.4.vsix`.
- 2026-07-16: Local compile, 13 tests, zero-high dependency audit, VSIX content inspection, real Chromium 300×720 normal/drag-state checks, and an authenticated Cloudflare deployment/read/delete acceptance all passed. The live acceptance proved a newly returned Workers URL can briefly return 404 before becoming 200, so production verification includes bounded retry.
- 2026-07-16: Wrangler `whoami` may exit successfully while printing that the user is unauthenticated. Authentication detection therefore parses the command output, Auto mode uses `--temporary` when unauthenticated, and retries with `--temporary` if non-interactive authentication disappears during deployment.
- 2026-07-16: User-facing sidebar, notifications, commands and settings support English and Simplified Chinese. `solodrop.language` defaults to following the VS Code display language and rerenders the sidebar immediately when changed.
- 2026-07-16: The sidebar header exposes a direct `中` / `EN` language toggle. It writes the selected language to the global VS Code `solodrop.language` setting, so the choice persists across reloads, restarts and workspaces.
- 2026-07-16: Recent-share metadata uses VS Code Settings Sync so the same signed-in user can see one list across devices. Local source paths are kept in a separate unsynced mapping; expired temporary shares reuse that local source when available and otherwise ask the user to choose the file before running the existing share flow.
- 2026-07-17: SoloDrop's managed link service is deployed as Cloudflare Worker `solodrop-links` on `https://drop.szlk.ai`, backed by one SQLite Durable Object. It accepts only verified SoloDrop `workers.dev` previews, creates seven-character short links, aligns temporary expiry, serves a platform-controlled action, counts visits, rate-limits creation and supports management-token deletion.
- 2026-07-17: The extension keeps the original verified preview as a fallback, verifies the managed short link before copying it, syncs share history through VS Code global state, and shows click counts in Recent without sending management tokens to the Webview. Sharing users do not configure the share-page action.

## Decisions

- 2026-07-18: The website share path uses private R2 storage with a 10 MiB limit instead of temporary Cloudflare Worker provisioning. This removes PoW/provisioning and route-propagation 404 checks from the website's critical path while keeping the extension's existing Wrangler deployment path unchanged.

- 2026-07-16: The product is an agent-artifact delivery layer, not a thin Cloudflare Drop wrapper. Format conversion, recipient readability, leak prevention and verified delivery are the product value.
- 2026-07-16: Auto deployment uses an authenticated Wrangler account when available and otherwise uses Cloudflare temporary deployment. Temporary links must be claimed within 60 minutes; custom expiry and private access are not presented as current features.
- 2026-07-16: Temporary entries derive an explicit 60-minute claim-window expiry, display active/expired status in Recent, and expose Share again only after expiry.
- 2026-07-16: The Logo source of truth is `resources/logo.svg`; `resources/logo.png` is the Marketplace raster derivative. The sidebar follows VS Code semantic theme tokens and maintains one primary action.
- 2026-07-17: Preview pages are content-first branded SoloDrop pages. The SoloDrop-owned action and attribution load after the artifact through `drop.szlk.ai/embed.js`; remote-component failure hides the action area and must not affect reading or download. Action copy and destination are platform policy, not plugin-user configuration.

## Current Handoff

- Goal: Keep web previews easy for recipients while giving sharing users control over lifetime, download presentation and review watermarks.
- Confirmed state: The R2 website path passed unit/build/dry-run checks, production deployment smoke, and an independent live acceptance covering create, inline read, escaped watermark, absent download button, download 403, CTA slot, authenticated token deletion and post-delete 404. The acceptance asset was deleted.
- Next useful action: Extend the same R2-backed persistent sharing policy to the VS Code extension only when explicitly requested; its current Wrangler path remains intentionally unchanged.
